I struggle with mindfulness vs a wandering mind that never shuts up and I find these meditations both soothing to my mind and energizing to my body. There are different lengths of time and multiple centers of focus to choose from. There is so much content in this app with more being added that it is definitely worth the price if you are committed to the practice...you have to actually practice to feel the benefits. The narrator is knowledgeable, relatable, and effective as both a meditation guide and teacher. It doesn't feel like a soothing siri is talking at you but rather like someone is actually guiding you through the meditation, as it should be.

Great for keeping you meditating. Having issues with downloading content for offline use. Third time reinstalling because I want to use the pain management pack offline. text: I don't usually write a review for an app, but this one deserves it. I tried nearly all meditation apps available to me and Headspace was the first app I had ever purchased. 100% worth it. So many options! You won't regret it!

text: A life changing app. I've been using mindfulness for a number of years, but this app has encouraged more focused and regular practice. It is expensive, unfortunately but definitely worth it. I hope the price comes down soon. Struggling to afford it.

I would like to share my personal experience with this app. I started out like many of you doing one or two 10 minute lessons a day, I quickly progressed and my meditations became deeper and deeper. One day during the silence of a guided meditation the app must have crashed. I was stuck in a deep trance without the voice to bring me back for what felt like only a few minutes, the next thing I remember I wake up in the year 2049 with total spiritual enlightenment and the knowledge of time travel. After spreading my wisdom and fixing the evils of the future I decided I must return to the year 2018 to write this review. 10/10 recommend this app

I have a problem of incessantly thinking, and my mind wanders off a little too often, and sometimes I even procrastinate and try to avoid meditating but when I do eventually come around to it, the process makes the mind so much calmer and focused. This is worth every penny that I paid for it. And it's cheap in India, only 2 dollars. :)

This app fixes everything wrong with the mindsets in the people who gave one star reviews, for this very thing they needed to look past their own shallow dismissal! Andy is great. why not; not buy mc donalds for a day, and pay for a month subscription? Ones more valuable then the other. Up to you, your path is your own.
